              "Dead": {
                "$type": "Models.PMF.Biomass, Models",
                "Name": "Biomass",
                "ResourceName": null,
                "Children": [],
                "Enabled": true,
                "ReadOnly": false
              },
              "Name": "Grain",
              "ResourceName": null,
              "Children": [
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Documentation, Models",
                  "Text": "**Grain Number**\n\nGrain number is calculated using the simple approach applied in earlier versions of the APSIM Wheat models where grain number is calculated directly from the mass of stem and spike atnthesis.  The parameter describing the potential number of grains per gram of the combined mass of stem and spike is commonly used as a cultivar-specific trait, often in concert with parameters for potential grain size.\n\n```\nGrainNumber = GrainsPerGramStemPlusSpike x StemPlusSpike.Wt\n```\n\nwhere\n \nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nGrainNumber | Grains per unit area | /m^2^\nStemPlusSpike.Wt | Mass of StemPlusSpike composite organ | g/m^2^\nGrainsPerGrainStemPlusSpike | Number of grains per gram of mass in Stem + Spike | /g\n\n\n**Grain Growth**\n\nGrain growth occurs in two  phases (Expansion and Filling) with a specific growth rate applied to both to allow grains to reach their potential size by the end of grain filling.\n\n```\nGrainDMDemand = PotentialGrainGrowthRate x ThermalTime x GrainNumber\n\nif in the GrainExpanding phenological phase\n   PotentialGrainGrowthRate = PotentialGrainSize x InitialProportion / GrainExpanding.Target\n\nelse if in the GrainFilling phenological phase\n   PotentialGrainGrowthRate = PotentialGrainSize x (1 -InitialProportion) / GrainFilling.Target\n\nPotentialGrainGrowthRate = bound (PotentialGrainGrowthRate, 0, PotentialGrainSize - GrainSize) x GrainNumber\n\n```\n\nwhere\n\nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nPotentialGrainGrowthRate | Potential daily increase in mean grain size | g/(^o^C.d)\nThermalTime | Daily thermal time increment calculated by the phenology model | ^o^C.d\nPotentialGrainSize | Grain size achievable by the plant under optimal growing conditions | g\nInitialProportion | Proportion of the PotentialGrainSize that is achieved by the end of the grain expansion phase | 0-1\nGrainExpanding.Target | Thermal time duration of the grain expansion phase | ^o^C.d\nGrainFilling.Target | Thermal time duration of the grain filling phase | ^o^C.d\n\n\n**Grain Nitrogen Accumulation**\n\nThe accumulation of nitrogen within the grain occurs in a single phase including both the grain expansion and filling phases.  Again, this is calculated from a specific grain N accumulation rate as described below.  Note also that the daily N demand is limited to ensure that N accumulation is slowed when grain growth is slowed.  The later is achieved by ensuring a maximum N concentration of daily grain growth.  Finally, all dry matter and nitrogen within the grain organ is assumed to be \"structural\", such that N cannot be retranslocated from grain and a minimum amount of N is required for any dry matter to be allocated to grain by the organ arbitrator.\n\n```\nPotentialGrainNAccumulationRate = PotentialGrainKernelN / (GrainExpanding.Target + GrainFilling.Target)\nGrainNDemand = PotentialGrainNAccumulationRate x ThermalTime x GrainNumber\nGrainNDemand = min (GrainNDemand, MaximumNConc x GrainDMDemand)\n\n```\n\nwhere\n\nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nPotentialGrainNAccumulationRate | Potential daily increase in grain kernel N content | g N/(^o^C.d)\nPotentialGrainKernelN | Grain kernel N content under optimum growing conditions| g N\nMaximumNConc | Maximum N concentration of daily growth (ie ratio of daily N and DM demand) | g N/g",
                  "Name": "Documentation",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.HoldFunction, Models",
                  "WhenToHold": "Anthesis",
                  "Name": "NumberFunction",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Functions.MultiplyFunction, Models",
                      "Name": "GrainNumber",
                      "ResourceName": null,
                      "Children": [
                        {
                          "$type": "Models.Functions.Constant, Models",
                          "FixedValue": 26.0,
                          "Units": "grains",
                          "Name": "GrainsPerGramOfStem",
                          "ResourceName": null,
                          "Children": [],
                          "Enabled": true,
                          "ReadOnly": false
                        },
