            {
              "$type": "Models.PMF.Organs.Root, Models",
              "DMSupply": null,
              "NSupply": null,
              "DMDemand": null,
              "NDemand": null,
              "potentialDMAllocation": null,
              "WaterUptakeSupply": null,
              "NitrogenUptakeSupply": null,
              "WaterTakenUp": null,
              "NitrogenTakenUp": null,
              "GrowthRespiration": 0.0,
              "MaintenanceRespiration": 0.0,
              "Name": "Root",
              "ResourceName": null,
              "Children": [
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Documentation, Models",
                  "Text": "\n**Dry Matter Demands**\n\nDemands for structural, metabolic and storage pools are provided to the organ arbitrator to simulate ongoing growth. In this model, all root material is assumed to be structural biomass.  The demands for each dry matter pool are therefore calculated as follows:\n\n```\n{[Wheat].Root.DMDemands.Structural.PotentialRootGrowth}\n{[Wheat].Root.DMDemands.Structural}\n{[Wheat].Root.DMDemands.Structural.StructuralFraction}\nStorage = 0\n{[Wheat].Root.DMDemands.Metabolic}\n```\n\nPotential root growth is calculated as a fraction of total plant growth as a function of growth stage.\n{[Wheat].Root.DMDemands.Structural.PotentialRootGrowth.PartitionFraction.PreGrainFilling.PartitionFraction}\n\n**Nitrogen Demand and Allocation**\n\nNitrogen allocation to structural, storage and metabolic biomass pools is calculated by the OrganArbitrator as described above.  The root model calculates the demands for each of these pools from information on the minimum, critical and maximum Nitrogen concentration for each predicted stage of development.\n\nThe minimum nitrogen concentration is used to describe the nitrogen content of the structural material. The difference between minimum and critical nitrogen concentration is assumed to correspond to metabolic stem material.  Storage nitrogen is equated with the difference between maximum and critical nitrogen concentrations.  In this model, all root root nitrogen is assumed to be structural. The values of each of these is therefore specified as follows.\n\n```\n// minimum, critical and maximum n concentrate are set to be equal\n// to provide a configuration where stem N is held in the structural pool only.\n{[Wheat].Root.MinimumNconc}\n{[Wheat].Root.CriticalNconc}\n{[Wheat].Root.MaximumNconc}\n```\n\n**Senescence and Detachment**\n\nRoot senescence and turnover is specified to occur throughout the entire crop.\n\n```\n{[Wheat].Root.SenescenceRate}\n```\n\n",
                  "Name": "Documentation",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
