            },
            {
              "$type": "Models.PMF.Organs.SimpleLeaf, Models",
              "Albedo": 0.25,
              "Gsmax350": 0.015,
              "R50": 150.0,
              "LeafInitialisationStage": "Emergence",
              "Height": 0.0,
              "BaseHeight": 0.0,
              "Width": 0.0,
              "FRGR": 0.0,
              "PotentialEP": 0.0,
              "WaterDemand": 0.0,
              "LightProfile": null,
              "KDead": 0.3,
              "LAIDead": 0.0,
              "DMSupply": null,
              "NSupply": null,
              "DMDemand": null,
              "NDemand": null,
              "potentialDMAllocation": null,
              "Name": "Leaf",
              "ResourceName": null,
              "Children": [
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Documentation, Models",
                  "Text": "\n\n**Canopy Development**\n\nLeaf area development is calculated as the net effect of leaf growth and senescence, removal of leaf by animals of management, and changes in specific leaf area of previous growth.  Note that all leaf growth in the model occurs before flag leaf.  The appearance of new tillers after flag leaf, as sometimes observed in the field, is not allowed for within this model.\n\n\nCalculations are as follows:\n \n```\n\nArea  = InitialArea + AccumulatedChange\nInitialArea = AreaPerPlant x Population\nAccumulatedChange = AreaGrowth - AreaSenesced - AreaRemoved - AreaShrinkage\nIf current growth stage is between emergence and flagleaf\n   AreaGrowth = AreaGrowth + SpecificLeafArea x Allocated.StructuralWt\nIf current growth stage is between emergence and HarvestRipe\n   AreaSenesced = AreaSenesced + SpecificLeafAreaCanopy x Senesced.StructuralWt\nIf current growth stage is between emergence and flagleaf\n   AreaRemoved = AreaRemoved + SpecificLeafAreaCanopy x Removed.StructuralWt\nIf current growth stage is between flagleaf and anthesis\n   AreaShrinkage = AreaSrhinkage SpecificLeafAreaCanopy x Live.StructuralWt x 0.2 x ThermalTime/TTFlagLeafToAnthesis\n\n```\n \nwhere\n \nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nArea | Green leaf area per unit ground area | m^2^/m^2^\nInitialArea | Leaf area of an individual plant at emerence | m^2^\nAreaGrowth | Accumulated leaf area growth from emergence to flag leaf | m^2^/m^2^\nAreaSenesced | Accumulated leaf area senescence from emergence to harvest ripe | m^2^/m^2^\nAreaRemoved | Accumulated leaf area removed (e.g. grazing) from emergence to harvest ripe| m^2^/m^2^\nAreaShrinkage | Accumulated leaf area reduction due to leaf shrinkage from flag leaf to anthesis| m^2^/m^2^\nSpecificLeafArea | Area per unit mass of green leaf for today's leaf growth | m^2^/g\nSpecificLeafAreaCanopy | Area per unit mass of green leaf currently in the entire crop canopy | m^2^/g\nAllocated.StructuralWt | Mass of dm allocated to the leaf from daily growth by the organ arbitrator. | g/m^2^\nSenesced.StructuralWt | Mass of live dm senesced on the current day. | g/m^2^\nRemoved.StructuralWt | Mass of live dm removed on the current day. | g/m^2^\nThermalTime | Daily thermal time calculated by the phenology model | ^o^C\nTTFlagLeafToAnthesis | Thermal time target for the period from Flag leaf to Anthesis | ^o^C\n\n\n**Potential Leaf Growth**\n\nPotential growth in leaf area is used to calculate the leaf dry matter demand.  The potential increase in leaf area is calculated with estimates of leaf appearance, stem dynamics and plant population.  The appearance and sizes of leaves are assumed to be similar on all stems.  Leaf size is assumed to increase from emergence to the beginning of stem elongation.  Leaf appearance is calculated within the Phenology model as part of the <a href=\"https://www.apsim.info/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/camp-model-description.docx\">CAMP</a> model.\n\nNote that leaf biomass is assumed to consist of entirely structural dry matter.\n\nCalculations are as follows:\n\n```\nif in vegetative phase (ie Emergence to Flag Leaf)\n   DMDemand.Structural.Wt = deltaLAIPotential x SpecificLeafArea\nelse\n   DMDemand.Structural.Wt = 0.0\nDMDemand.Storage.Wt = 0.0\nDMDemand.Metabolic.Wt = 0.0\nDeltaLAIPotential = AreaLargestLeaf x RelativeArea x Population x StemNumberPerPlant x LAR x ExpansionStressFactor\nLAR = ThermalTime / Phyllochron\n\n\n```\n\nwhere\n \nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nDMDemand.Structural.Wt | Daily potential leaf structural growth (ie daily DMD demand for leaf growth) | g/m<sup>2</sup>\ndeltaLAIPotential | Daily potential increase in LAI if DM supply from arbitrator is adequate | m<sup>2</sup>/m<sup>2</sup>/d\nAreaLargestLeaf | The area of the largest leaf on the main stem. | m<sup>2</sup>\nRelativeArea | The size of the currently expanding leaf compared to the largest leaf on the main stem | 0-1\nStemNumberPerPlant | The number of currently expanding stems on each plant. | /plant\nLAR | The Leaf Appearance Rate, or the number of leaves appearing on the current day. | /day\nThermalTime | Daily thermal time calculated by the phenology model | <sup>o</sup>C\nPhyllochron | The thermal time required for the appearance of each leaf on the main stem. | <sup>o</sup>C\n\n\n**Tiller Dynamics**\n\nThe number of stems on each plant is calculated by adding an accumulation of the daily tillering rate to the main stem.  Tillering rate is driven by main stem leaf number to account for the appearance of the main stem tillers with each main stem leaf after leaf three and each higher order tiller after the third leaf on each sub-tiller.  Tillering will occur at optimum rates whilst canopy cover is less than 20% and cease whenever cover is above 80%.\n\nCalculations are as follows:\n\n```\nStemNumberPerPlant = 1.0 + TillerNumber - DeadTillerNumber\nTillerNumber = sum of (DeltaHS x TilleringRate) from Emergence to PanicleInitiation\nTilleringRate = PotentialTilleringRate x min(ExpansionStress, CoverEffect)\nDeadTillerNumber = sum of (TillerNumber x TillerAttritionRate) from PanicleInitiation to MaximumGrainLength\nTillerAttritionRate = function returning zero when GrowthRatePerTiller is above 0.03, increasing to 0.03/d when GrowthRatePerTiller is zero.\nGrowthRatePerTiller = five day moving average of (DailyGrowth / ThermalTime / StemPopulation\n\n```\n\nwhere\n \nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nStemNumberPerPlant | Total number of stems on each plant (main stem and tillers) | /plant\nTillerNumber | Total number of tillers on each plant (including first, second, third,... order tillers. | /plant\nDeadTillerNumber | Number of dead tillers on each plant | /plant\nTilleringRate | Number of tillers appearing anywhere on the plant during the current day | /day\nPotentialTilleringRate | Potential number of tillers that could appear today in the absence of limiting factors| /day\nExpansionStress | Rate modifier accounting for the effect of water, nitrogen or temperature. | 0-1\nTillerAttritionRate | Proportion of live stems dying on the current day | /d\nCoverEffect | Rate modifier accounting for the effect of shading on tiller appearance. | 0-1\nStemPopulation | Number of stems per unit area | /m<sup>2</sup>\nGrowthRatePerTiller | Expression of daily growth rate relative to thermal time and tiller number | g/<sup>o</sup>C.d\n\n\n**Specific Green Leaf Area**\n\nThe winter cereal model estimates the specific leaf area of daily leaf growth directly rather than as an emergent property of separate area and mass growth functions as used in many earlier APSIM wheat models.  An optimal SpecificLeafArea is reduced below 15^o^C to a factor of 50% at a mean daily temperature of 5^o^C.  A WaterTensionFactor (provided by the Root Model) is used to capture effects of low leaf water potential on SpecificLeafArea and this will reduce SpecificLeafArea by 50% at a WaterTensionFactor of 0.8.  These will result in a maximum reduction in SpecificLeafArea of 50% of the optimum value under either water or temperature limitation.\n\n```\nSpecificLeafArea = PotentialSpecificLeafArea x min (SWFactor, TemperatureFactor)\n```\n\nwhere\n \nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nSpecificLeafArea | Area per unit mass of green leaf for today's leaf growth | m<sup>2</sup>/g\nPotentialSpecificLeafArea | SpecificLeafArea for daily leaf growth under optimal growing conditions | m<sup>2</sup>/g\nSWFactor | Water Factor to reduce SpecificLeafArea under water limiting conditions | 0-1\nTemperatureFactor | Temperature Factor to reduce SpecificLeafArea under low temperature conditions | 0-1\n\n**Canopy Light Extinction Coefficients**\n\nCanopy light interception is calculated by the methods described above (see light interception section in this chapter) using light extinction coefficients.  The extinction coefficient for green leaf is assumed to change with plant growth stage and row spacing.  The extinction coefficient is assumed to have a higher value up until EndJuvenile growth stage with leaves on small plants often falling more horizontally for this early growth.  This initial value is a function of row spacing with a value of 0.9 at row spacing up to 150mm, decreasing to 0.7 at 500mm row spacing. Extinction coefficient then falls to a lower, stable (and row spacing independant) value once crops reach flag leaf stage.\n\n```\nExtinctionCoefficient = LateVegetativeValue + (EarlyGrowthValue - LateVegetativeValue) x DevelopmentFactor\n\n```\n\nwhere\n \nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nExtinctionCoefficient | Daily light extinction coefficient for green leaf area for the current day | -\nLateVegetativeValue | The value of daily lignt extinction coefficient for canopies after flag leaf stage | -\nEarlyGrowthValue | The value of daily light extinction coefficient for canopies prior to double ridge | -\nDevelopmentFactor | A function to scale  daily light extinction coefficient between double ridge and flag leaf stages | -\n",
                  "Name": "Documentation",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
                {
