            {
              "$type": "Models.PMF.Organs.GenericOrgan, Models",
              "StartLive": null,
              "DMSupply": null,
              "NSupply": null,
              "DMDemand": null,
              "NDemand": null,
              "potentialDMAllocation": null,
              "IsAboveGround": true,
              "Name": "Spike",
              "ResourceName": null,
              "Children": [
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Documentation, Models",
                  "Text": "\n**Spike Dry Matter Demands**\n\nDemands for structural, metabolic and storage pools are provided to the organ arbitrator to simulate ongoing spike growth.  The demands for each dry matter pool are calculated as follows:\n\n```\n{[Wheat].Spike.PotentialGrowth}\n   {[Wheat].Spike.PotentialGrowth.EmergenceToRapidGrainFill.PotentialGrowth}\n   {[Wheat].Spike.PotentialGrowth.EmergenceToRapidGrainFill.PotentialGrowth.TargetWt}\n   {[Wheat].Spike.PotentialGrowth.EmergenceToRapidGrainFill.PotentialGrowth.TargetWt.PotentialAboveGroundWt}\n\n{[Wheat].Spike.DMDemands.Structural}\n{[Wheat].Spike.DMDemands.Structural.StructuralFraction}\n\n{[Wheat].Spike.DMDemands.Storage}\n{[Wheat].Spike.DMDemands.Metabolic}\n\n\n```\n\nThe fraction of daily growth partitioned to stems is specified as a function of growth stage.\n\n{[Wheat].Spike.PotentialGrowth.EmergenceToRapidGrainFill.PotentialGrowth.TargetWt.SpikeFraction}\n\n**Spike Nitrogen Demand and Allocation**\n\nSpike Nitrogen allocation to structural, storage and metabolic biomass pools is calculated by the OrganArbitrator as described above.  The spike model calculates the demands for each of these pools from information on the minimum, critical and maximum stem Nitrogen concentration for each predicted stage of development.\n\nThe minimum spike nitrogen concentration is used to describe the nitrogen content of the structural spike material. The difference between minimum and critical nitrogen concentration is assumed to correspond to metabolic spike material.  Storage nitrogen is equated with the difference between maximum and critical nitrogen concentrations.  The values of each of these is specified as follows.\n\n```\n// minimum and critical are set to be equal to provide a configuration where spike N is held in structural and storage pools only.\n{[Wheat].Spike.MinimumNconc}\n{[Wheat].Spike.CriticalNconc}\n```\nStorage N is parameterised therefore as the difference between minimum/critical N concentration and the following maximum N concentration.\n{[Wheat].Spike.MaximumNconc}\n\n**Senescence and Detachment**\n\nSpike senescence is specified to occur after the end of grain filling such that there is total spike senescence by the harvest ripe phase.  \n\n```\nif the current growth stage is between EndGrainFill and HarvestRip\n   SenescenceRate = min (1.0, ThermalTime/ThermalTimeRemaining)\nThermalTimeRemaining = GrainFilling.Target - GrainFilling.ProgressThroughPhase\n{[Wheat].Spike.DetachmentRateFunction}\n\n```\n\nwhere\n\nName | Description | Units\n-|-|-\nSenescenceRate | Fraction of live spike that senesces on the current day | /day\nThermalTime | Daily thermal time calculated by the phenology model | <sup>o</sup>C\nThermalTimeRemaining | Amount of thermal time remaining within the Grain Filling phase | <sup>o</sup>C\nGrainFilling.Target | Total amount of thermal time required to meet the grain filling phase |  <sup>o</sup>C\nGrainFilling.ProgressThroughPhase | Total thermal time already accumulated within the grain filling phase | <sup>o</sup>C\n\n**DM and N reuse within the plant**\n\nNon-structural DM and N (ie storage or metabolic pools) can be available for reuse elsewhere within the plant to meet other demands via reallocation of DM or N from senescing biomass or retranslocation from live biomass during some growth phases (e.g. reallocation of N from senescing stem or retranslocation from stem N storage to support protein accumulation in grain during grain filling.  The potential fraction of DM or N that is available on any day is specified as follows:\n\n```\n{[Wheat].Spike.DMRetranslocationFactor}\n{[Wheat].Spike.DMReallocationFactor}\n{[Wheat].Spike.NRetranslocationFactor}\n{[Wheat].Spike.NReallocationFactor}\n\n```",
                  "Name": "Documentation",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.Constant, Models",
                  "FixedValue": 1.0,
                  "Units": null,
                  "Name": "NReallocationFactor",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.Constant, Models",
                  "FixedValue": 0.0,
                  "Units": null,
                  "Name": "RemobilisationCost",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.PhaseLookup, Models",
                  "Name": "NRetranslocationFactor",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Functions.PhaseLookupValue, Models",
                      "Start": "Emergence",
                      "End": "MaximumGrainLength",
                      "Name": "EarlyGrowth",
                      "ResourceName": null,
                      "Children": [
                        {
                          "$type": "Models.Functions.Constant, Models",
                          "FixedValue": 0.0,
                          "Units": null,
                          "Name": "ValueDuringEarlyGrowth",
                          "ResourceName": null,
                          "Children": [],
                          "Enabled": true,
                          "ReadOnly": false
                        }
                      ],
                      "Enabled": true,
                      "ReadOnly": false
                    },
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Functions.PhaseLookupValue, Models",
                      "Start": "MaximumGrainLength",
                      "End": "EndGrainFill",
                      "Name": "ReproductiveGrowth",
                      "ResourceName": null,
                      "Children": [
                        {
                          "$type": "Models.Functions.Constant, Models",
                          "FixedValue": 0.1,
                          "Units": null,
                          "Name": "ValueDuringGrainFill",
                          "ResourceName": null,
                          "Children": [],
                          "Enabled": true,
                          "ReadOnly": false
                        }
                      ],
                      "Enabled": true,
                      "ReadOnly": false
                    }
                  ],
                  "Enabled": true,
                  "ReadOnly": false
                },
                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.LinearInterpolationFunction, Models",
                  "Name": "MaximumNConc",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Functions.XYPairs, Models",
